4
00:00:09,570 --> 00:00:12,570
So alternate navigation in edX is this ability

5
00:00:12,570 --> 00:00:15,420
to kind of add custom navigation to a course.

6
00:00:15,420 --> 00:00:19,420
You can give a course a more custom look that sets it apart from other courses.

7
00:00:19,420 --> 00:00:22,170
It's particularly nice, because, as I'm sure you realize,

8
00:00:22,170 --> 00:00:24,717
edX is a very linear progression through the course material

9
00:00:24,717 --> 00:00:27,300
if you just go through the outline or the horizontal bars that

10
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:28,620
are on the course pages.

11
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:32,547
And this alternative navigation lets learners see pathways

12
00:00:32,547 --> 00:00:35,130
through the material that is not necessarily just from A to B.

13
00:00:35,130 --> 00:00:39,000
So you can connect things that maybe are in section one to section eight

14
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,860
that otherwise you could just do with edX's default look.

15
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:46,560
It's also nice, because you can expose the entire course layout on a page.

16
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:50,670
So right now, default edX look, you can only see that on the outline.

17
00:00:50,670 --> 00:00:53,760
But you could put course navigation on a single page

18
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:56,160
that shows where everything is.

19
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:59,670
